<p class="article-lead">Alcohol-free perfume manufacturing is not simply standard perfume with ethanol removed. The
    carrier changes clarity, skin feel, spray behavior, preservation considerations and fragrance performance.</p>
<h2>Choose the format first</h2>
<p>Oil roll-ons, water-based sprays and other low- or no-alcohol systems need different formulas and packages. A
    water-containing product may require solubilization and microbiological controls; an oil may need a roller or compatible
    pump rather than a fine-mist sprayer.</p>
<h2>Test the complete product</h2>
<p>Assess separation, haze, odor change, color, leakage and application over time. Check gasket, dip tube and container
    compatibility with the actual carrier. Claims such as “alcohol free” should be verified against the formula and reviewed
    under destination-market rules.</p>